{
  "texts": [
    "Our deep-learning model is a standard multilayer-perceptron feedforward artificial neural network that is widely used for blind function approximation without any a priori knowledge (see ref.",
    "Hji and we use the Adam optimizer with its default learning rate of 10 À3 and a batch size of 10.",
    "Three quarters of the calibration data are used for training, and the remainder for validation.",
    "We train until the validation loss has not improved for three epochs, and we restore the weights that corresponded to the best validation loss.",
    "We found that the results are not very sensitive to the exact choice of hyperparameters."
  ]
}